<h3><i class="mch-search"></i> <img src="../../images/smart-1-1-magnifying-glass.jpg" alt="Image of Magnifying Glass" class="right ppic" />REVIEW. Aligning Learning with an Implementation Model</h3>

<h3>Implementation Model</h3>
    <p>The Community Expertise and Perspectives Framework, adapted from the National Academy of Medicine's model for assessing community engagement, provides a foundation for meaningfully incorporating community expertise throughout all phases of work. This framework emphasizes that individuals with practical knowledge must be central to informing and guiding decisions that affect their lives. The model identifies four areas of action that serve as a framework for valuing community expertise: (1) Strengthened Partnerships, (2) Expanded Knowledge, (3) Improved Programs and Policies, and (4) Thriving Communities.¹</p>
    <p><img src="../../images/smart-implementation-framework-8b.png" width="531" height="" alt=""/></p>
